    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276120\">Nicolas Blanco</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229136-category-theory/topic/enchilada.20categories/near/191727246\" title=\"#narrow/stream/229136-category-theory/topic/enchilada.20categories/near/191727246\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A naive question: You said that looking at the bicategory is better. Would it make sense to look at the double category instead (with *-homomorphisms as vertical arrows and correspondences as horizontal arrows)?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Not David, but I get the feeling people know how to work with bicategories better than they do with double categories. By \"better\", I think David meant that it's better <em>than</em> merely looking at the homotopy category.</p>",
        "id": 191831748,
        "sender_full_name": "(=_=)",
        "timestamp": 1585186445
