    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276120\">Nicolas Blanco</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229136-category-theory/topic/enchilada.20categories/near/191860227\" title=\"#narrow/stream/229136-category-theory/topic/enchilada.20categories/near/191860227\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Yes, I had in mind this rough analogy with the (pseudo-?)double category of rings, ring homomorphisms and bimodules. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is precisely the analogy pursued by Meyer, although he's only interested in it as a bicategory AFAIK.</p>",
